@himansu_007: I have done all while ago (on mininova) and I would try to find living copies, but chances are slim to none.
And - request are "frozen" indeed till Xmas.

@megodtoo: You saved even more. Ever single The Town XviD totally fell apart more times - anyone can watch from 1h55 - 1h56 when Hamm say "We are national organization." and how video - in all encodes except Diamond's - completely fell apartin next seconds... 

This is because of stupid need "to be first" and therefore P2P nowadays use 1-pass encoding to save the time.

That goes on cost of us - suckers, and I would never understand why so many people burn so many terabytes every time, downloading total shit and came here to voice their frustrations out.
